Metadata: Three new and bioactive icosanoids from the temperate red marine alga "Farlowia mollis."

Three new dihydroxyicosan​oids have been isolated from a previously unstudied temperate red marine alga, "Farlowia mollis" (Cryptonemiales​, Rhodophyta), and their structures have been deduced. Collectively, these new natural products modulate fMLP- induced superoxide anion generation in human neutrophils, inhibit the conversion of arachidonic acid to lipoxygenase products by human neutrophils, and inhibit the functioning of the dog kidney Na+/K+-ATPase.
